==South Levantine Arabic==
{{phrasebook|ajp}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|ajp|ar|مَرْحَبًا}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{ajp-IPA|marḥaba<p:ˈmɑr.ħɑ.bɑ>}}
* {{audio|ajp|LL-Q55633582 (ajp)-AdrianAbdulBaha-مرحبا.wav|a=Ramallah}}

===Interjection===
{{ajp-interjection|tr=marḥaba}}

# [[hello]]
#: {{syn|ajp|هلا|tr=hala|q=informal}}

====Usage notes====
* People usually respond to {{m-self|ajp|مرحبا|tr=marḥaba}} with its dual or plural form:
** {{m|ajp|مرحبتين|tr=marḥabtēn|lit=two hellos}}
** {{m|ajp|مراحب|tr=marāḥeb|lit=many hellos}}

